object.script:
CLOSED = 0 OPENING_ROTATE = 1 OPENING_SLIDE = 2 OPEN = 3 CLOSING_SLIDE = 4 CLOSING_ROTATE = 5
ROTOR_ANGLE = -0.08 SLIDER_SPEED = 1 ROTATE_TICKS = 20 SLIDE_TICKS = 90
state = CLOSED rotorOutput = 0 sliderOutput = 0 count = 0
function onTick() local pressed = input.getBool(1)
if state == CLOSED then if pressed then rotorOutput = ROTOR_ANGLE count = ROTATE_TICKS state = OPENING_ROTATE end elseif state == OPENING_ROTATE then count = count - 1 if count <= 0 then sliderOutput = SLIDER_SPEED state = OPENING_SLIDE count = SLIDE_TICKS end elseif state == OPENING_SLIDE then count = count - 1 if count <= 0 then sliderOutput = 0 state = OPEN end elseif state == OPEN then if pressed then sliderOutput = -SLIDER_SPEED state = CLOSING_SLIDE count = SLIDE_TICKS end elseif state == CLOSING_SLIDE then count = count - 1 if count <= 0 then sliderOutput = 0 state = CLOSING_ROTATE rotorOutput = 0 count = ROTATE_TICKS end elseif state == CLOSING_ROTATE then count = count - 1 if count <= 0 then state = CLOSED end end
output.setNumber(1, rotorOutput) output.setNumber(2, sliderOutput) output.setNumber(3, state) end

object.script:
INIT = 0 OPENING = 1 OPEN = 2 CLOSING = 3 CLOSED = 4
TOP_ROTOR_OPEN = 0 TOP_ROTOR_CLOSED = -1 BOTTOM_ROTOR_OPEN = 0.6 BOTTOM_ROTOR_CLOSED = -1 TICKS_TO_MOVE = 60
state = INIT topRotorOutput = 0 bottomRotorOutput = 0 count = 0
function onTick() local pressed = input.getBool(1)
if state == INIT then topRotorOutput = TOP_ROTOR_OPEN bottomRotorOutput = BOTTOM_ROTOR_OPEN count = TICKS_TO_MOVE state = OPENING elseif state == OPENING then count = count - 1 if count <= 0 then state = OPEN end elseif state == OPEN then if pressed then topRotorOutput = TOP_ROTOR_CLOSED bottomRotorOutput = BOTTOM_ROTOR_CLOSED state = CLOSING count = TICKS_TO_MOVE end elseif state == CLOSING then count = count - 1 if count <= 0 then state = CLOSED end elseif state == CLOSED then if pressed then topRotorOutput = TOP_ROTOR_OPEN bottomRotorOutput = BOTTOM_ROTOR_OPEN count = TICKS_TO_MOVE state = OPENING end end
output.setNumber(1, topRotorOutput) output.setNumber(2, bottomRotorOutput) output.setNumber(3, state) end

function makematC(phi, the, psi) mar = { {co(the)*co(psi), si(phi)*si(the)*co(psi)-co(phi)*si(psi), co(phi)*si(the)*co(psi)+si(phi)*si(psi)}, {co(the)*si(psi), si(phi)*si(the)*si(psi)+co(phi)*co(psi), co(phi)*si(the)*si(psi)-si(phi)*co(psi)}, {-si(the), si(phi)*co(the), co(phi)*co(the)} } return mar end
function rotate(mat, vec) temp = {0, 0, 0} for i=1, 3 do ali = 0 for j=1, 3 do ali = ali + mat[i][j] * vec[j] end temp[i] = ali end return temp end
function Mtrans(maa) for i=1, 3 do for j=1, 3 do grr[j][i] = maa[i][j] end end return grr end
function onTick()
sn(1,gn(1))--Map X sn(2,gn(3))--Map Y sn(3,gn(2))--Altitude
EFB = makematC(gn(4), gn(5), gn(6))
cphi = -at(EFB[2][1],EFB[2][2]) cthe = as(EFB[2][3]) cpsi = at(EFB[3][3], EFB[1][3])
sn(4, cphi)--roll sn(5, cthe)--pitch sn(6, mod(pi2*1.25-cpsi,pi2))--nautical azimuth(North:0, clockwise, 0->+pi2) sn(21,cpsi)--raw azimuth(East:0, counterclockwise, -pi<-0->+pi), for calc. use
rot = {gn(10),gn(11),gn(12)} MAG = Mtrans(EFB) ang = rotate(MAG, rot)
--eul = {cphi, cthe, -cpsi} AMS = makematC(cphi,cthe,-cpsi) vel = {gn(9),gn(7),-gn(8)} for i=1,3 do sn(i+6, vel[i]) end --7~9 : local linear speed, x:forward +, y:right +, z:downward +
sn(10, -ang[3]*pi2) sn(11, -ang[1]*pi2) sn(12, ang[2]*pi2) --10~12: local angular speed, roll, pitch, yaw
sn(19,gn(13))--abs. linear speed sn(20,gn(17))--compass, for compatibility, not recomended
--tiltx = cthe/pi2 --tilty = as(-si(cphi)*co(cthe))/pi2 tiltz = as(-co(cphi)*co(cthe))/pi2
sn(16,gn(15))--tilt x sn(17,gn(16))--tilt y sn(18,tiltz)--tilt z, for compatibility
vew = rotate(AMS, vel) sn(13, vew[1]) sn(14, -vew[2]) sn(15, -vew[3]) --13~15: world linear speed, X:East +, Y:North +, Z:upward +
end
